<subSubSection id="51FBEEFE34564774FF7EF8CDA7CCB3D3" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="195EBD7534564777FF7EF8CDA67CB4AD" blockId="1.[151,1436,1721,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="2B95616734564777FF7EF8CDA61DB41D" bold="true" box="[199,315,1793,1818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from unknown number of specimens (
<bibRefCitation id="7D70C08434564777FBF1F8CDA3D1B41D" author="Breddin" box="[1096,1271,1793,1818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" refString="Breddin, G. (1901 a) Die Hemipteren von Celebes. Ein Beitrag zur Faunistik der Insel. Abhandlungen der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft zu Halle, 24, 1 - 215, 1 plate." type="book chapter" year="1901" yearSuffix="a">
Breddin 
<number id="AF29AF5234564777FB16F8CEA3CCB41D" box="[1199,1258,1794,1818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" value="1901.0">1901</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
). The original description and label data provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="7D70C08434564777FDFEF8E9A5D9B439" author="Breddin" box="[583,767,1829,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" refString="Breddin, G. (1901 a) Die Hemipteren von Celebes. Ein Beitrag zur Faunistik der Insel. Abhandlungen der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft zu Halle, 24, 1 - 215, 1 plate." type="book chapter" year="1901" yearSuffix="a">
Breddin (
<number id="AF29AF5234564777FD09F8EAA5CFB439" box="[688,745,1830,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" value="1901.0">1901</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
perfectly fit with the specimen examined during the present study therefore it is recognized as a 
<typeStatus id="C65A03D734564777FD8BF886A5AFB465" box="[562,649,1866,1890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">syntype</typeStatus>
and is hereby designated as 
<typeStatus id="C65A03D734564777FC76F885A31CB465" box="[975,1082,1865,1890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">lectotype</typeStatus>
. Four specimens of this variety are present in 
<collectionCode id="7FF025B034564777FE81F8A2A65FB481" box="[312,377,1902,1926]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">DEIC</collectionCode>
(S.M. Blank, 
<emphasis id="2B95616734564777FDA2F8A2A582B482" box="[539,676,1902,1925]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">pers. comm.</emphasis>
), those are probably 
<typeStatus id="C65A03D734564777FC2CF8A2A4D1B481" box="[917,1015,1902,1926]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">syntypes</typeStatus>
too. They were not examined during the present study.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="195EBD7534564774FF7EF879A7CCB3D3" blockId="1.[151,1436,1721,2034]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,212]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">
This variety has apparently not been cited after its original description (
<bibRefCitation id="7D70C08434564777FBB5F879A3B3B4C9" author="Slater" box="[1036,1173,1973,1998]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" refString="Slater, J. A. (1964) A catalogue of the Lygaeidae of the world. Vols. I - II. University of Connecticut, Storrs, XVIII + 1668 pp. [I: I - XVIII, 1 - 778; II: 779 - 1668]" type="book chapter" year="1964">
Slater 
<number id="AF29AF5234564777FBE0F879A3B3B4C9" box="[1113,1173,1973,1998]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The single examined specimen indeed represents 
<taxonomicName id="DEE1C6F634564777FE5CF815A4B8B4F5" authority="Fabricius, 1794" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1794" box="[485,926,2009,2034]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Spilostethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hospes">
<emphasis id="2B95616734564777FE5CF815A5E0B4F6" box="[485,710,2009,2033]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Spilostethus hospes</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 
<number id="AF29AF5234564777FCE3F816A4B0B4F5" box="[858,918,2010,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" value="1794.0">1794</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, a species widely distributed from 
<collectingCountry id="61F6FDE534564777FAF5F816A25FB4F6" box="[1356,1401,2010,2033]" name="Iran" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Iran</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="61F6FDE534554774FF2EFF54A7D1B3A8" box="[151,247,152,175]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
. The variety 
<emphasis id="2B95616734554774FE29FF54A525B3B7" box="[400,515,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">celebensis</emphasis>
has no taxonomic value and it should be considered as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="DEE1C6F634554774FA3EFF54A7C5B3D3" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Spilostethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hospes">
<emphasis id="2B95616734554774FA3EFF54A7C5B3D3" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">S. hospes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
